initialize(address,string,string,string,.details: Function to create a new edition. Can only be called by the allowed creator Sets the only allowed minter to the address that creates/owns the edition. This can be re-assigned or updated later

params._animationHash: The associated hash of the animation in sha-256 bytes32 format. If animation is omitted the hash can be zero.
params._animationUrl: Animation URL of the edition. Not required, but if omitted image URL needs to be included. This follows the opensea spec for NFTs
params._description: Description of edition, used in the description field of the NFT
params._editionSize: Number of editions that can be minted in total. If 0, unlimited editions can be minted.
params._imageHash: SHA256 of the given image in bytes32 format (0xHASH). If no image is included, the hash can be zero.
params._imageUrl: Image URL of the edition. Strongly encouraged to be used, if necessary, only animation URL can be used. One of animation and image url need to exist in a edition to render the NFT.
params._name: Name of edition, used in the title as "$NAME NUMBER/TOTAL"
params._owner: User that owns and can mint the edition, gets royalty and sales payouts and can update the base url if needed.
params._royaltyBPS: BPS of the royalty set on the contract. Can be 0 for no royalty.
params._startTime: Time that purchasing will be available
params._symbol: Symbol of the new token contract

mintEdition(address).details: This mints a single edition to the given address.

params.to: address to send the newly minted edition to

mintEditions(address[]).details: This mints multiple editions to the given list of addresses.

params.recipients: list of addresses to send the newly minted editions to

prePurchase(bytes32[]).details: This allows the user on the allowlist to purchase an edition at the given price in the contract before the sale start time.

params.proof: merkle proof that sender is on the allowlist

purchase().details: This allows the user to purchase an edition at the given price in the contract.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params.newContractURI: The URI of the new contract metadata

setMerkleRoot(bytes32).details: This sets the merkle root, which controls what wallets are on the allowlist and allowed to mint during the pre-mint.

params._merkleRoot: is the precalculated merkle root for a given state of the allowlist.

setSalePrice(uint256).details: This sets a simple ETH sales price Setting a sales price allows users to mint the edition until it sells out. For more granular sales, use an external sales contract.

params._salePrice: if sale price is 0 sale is stopped, otherwise that amount of ETH is needed to start the sale.

params._startTime: The UNIX timestamp when purchases will be allowed to be made

tokenURI(uint256).details: Get URI for given token id

params.tokenId: token id to get uri for

totalSupply().details: returns the number of minted tokens within the edition

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

updateEditionURLs(string,string).details: Allows for updates of edition urls by the owner of the edition. Only URLs can be updated (data-uris are supported), hashes cannot be updated.

withdraw().details: This withdraws ETH from the contract to the contract owner.

numberCanMint().notice: Returns the number of editions allowed to mint (max_uint256 when open edition)

userdoc.notice: This is a smart contract for handling dynamic contract minting.
